			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Just a note on having &quot;fun&quot; sicking a befriended or charmed animal on the PoD.  <BR>
The attacked MOB (PoD in this case) knows who controls the pet.  You may wish to<BR>
make exit rapidly after sending in the pet.  I know.  I tried this early in level 14 and<BR>
learned that a &quot;safe distance&quot; needs to be well out of sight.  I have not tried twice to<BR>
see just how far you have to be away from PoD to avoid being killed instantly and well<BR>
before you get a chance to watch the fight with the guards.  It's more fun to sick bats<BR>
on orc pawns in the newbie zone and watch the newbies gawk.<BR>
<BR>
Fellrod - Druid of the 19th Circle
				</font>
